snippet.textDisplay:
There is something called overproduction, which is happening to Indian Coke Studio. The song is phenomenal, and the singers are absolutely brilliant! But the accompanying paraphernalia takes away from it. It has become like any other Bollywood production. We don't need that—we already have that. The beauty of Coke Studio when it started was its simplicity, connection with the artist, the raw voice of the musicians, and the gems produced then. It is like an ostentatious display of production money. 
If I compare this to Coke Studio from Pakistan and Bangladesh, they are a treat to watch and listen to because they have kept the simplicity alive.
snippet.textOriginal:

The beauty of Coke Studio when it started was its simplicity, connection with the artist, the raw voice of the musicians, and the gems produced then. It is like an ostentatious display of production money. 
If I compare this to Coke Studio from Pakistan and Bangladesh, they are a treat to watch and listen to because they have kept the simplicity alive.
